1.  Add new features and fix bugs.
2.  Search for TODO:RELEASE and fix those.
3.  Fix bugs.
4.  Check the following fields in PackageInfo.g:
    Version, Date, ArchiveURL.
5.  Check the version in init.g, README, Makefile, buildman.config, check NEWS.
6.  Check docs.
7.  Run tst/test-release.sh.
8.  Commit.
9.  Run 'make dist' to create three tarballs.
10. Upload them to sf.net as described at 
    http://alexandria.wiki.sourceforge.net/File+Release+System+-+Offering+Files+for+Download#upload
11. Go to http://sourceforge.net/projects/finautom > Admin > File releases.
    Create new release, add files.
12. Download fresh tarball from http://sf.net, install it, run tests.
    Restart from step 2 if needed.
13. Unpack a tarball and upload its content to the web site, as described at 
    http://alexandria.wiki.sourceforge.net/Project+Web,+Shell,+VHOST+and+Database+Services
14. Change version and date in index.html
15. Check http://finautom.sf.net, click around. Restart from step 3 if needed.
16. Tag the release.
17. Done.
